    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="644"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName
                        corresp="#p_DA1">Dulles</persName> papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Director of Central Intelligence</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_DA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dulles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>personal and private</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-29">May 29,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I received the following eyes only message for you from <persName
                        corresp="#p_SWB1">Bedell</persName> sent Geneva Saturday, May 29.</p>
                <p>“Please give this privately to <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Foster</persName>
                    preferably by phone as soon as convenient after he arrives in New York on
                    Tuesday. <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Bedell</persName> is convinced that
                        <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BG1"
                        >Bidault</persName> are willing to accept <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        >Foster</persName>’s leadership and judgment on matter of Thai Resolution
                    but they would like to be sure that decisions are his, personally, and taken
                    after he has personally considered their respective problems. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>’s position vis-à-vis India particularly
                    difficult now as result of <persName corresp="#p_DA1">Allen</persName>’s
                    statement to <persName corresp="#p_PNR1">Pillai</persName> re British support.
                    This statement was made before <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> had
                    informed <persName corresp="#p_MVKK1">Krishna Menon</persName>, which he did
                    this morning, with bad reaction.”</p>
            </div>
